Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.52,0:00:04.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The culture festival is finally drawing near...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.19,0:00:08.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...so our days have been filled with nothing but preparations.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.27,0:00:10.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yano, where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.03,0:00:12.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, have you seen Yano?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.03,0:00:16.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, Yano? I think he's around here somewhere, so I'll take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.46,0:00:29.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure that's really all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.09,0:00:30.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.51,0:00:33.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One thing I'm especially good at...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.38,0:00:35.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.43,0:00:36.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.26,0:00:40.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...is finding Yano, whenever or wherever he may be.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.10,0:00:43.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yano.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.35,0:00:48.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because he's the one I love.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.03,0:01:05.92,Romaji OP S,,0000,0000,0000,,Usotsuki na anata nakimushi no atashi
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.92,0:01:11.88,Romaji OP S,,0000,0000,0000,,Doushite umaku ikanai wa
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.88,0:01:18.01,Romaji OP S,,0000,0000,0000,,Oshare shita kami mo rain suton no tsume mo
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.01,0:01:23.98,Romaji OP S,,0000,0000,0000,,Anata wa kidzuki mo shinai ne
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.98,0:01:31.36,Romaji OP S,,0000,0000,0000,,Love kanashii namida nanka ja nai yo
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.36,0:01:36.07,Romaji OP S,,0000,0000,0000,,Me ga kawaite hirihiri suru dake
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.07,0:01:41.99,Romaji OP S,,0000,0000,0000,,Kono unmei bakari I love
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.91,0:01:50.88,Romaji OP S,,0000,0000,0000,,Kimi dake wo atashi dake wo
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.88,0:01:55.80,Romaji OP S,,0000,0000,0000,,Atsui omoi wo uketomete
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.01,0:02:02.93,Romaji OP S,,0000,0000,0000,,Doko made mo tsunagattetai
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.93,0:02:09.69,Romaji OP S,,0000,0000,0000,,Kawaikunai nakigao mo se mo aishiteru
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.03,0:01:05.92,english OP S,,0000,0000,0000,,Why can't things go well between
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.92,0:01:11.88,english OP S,,0000,0000,0000,,the liar, you, and the crybaby, me?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.88,0:01:18.01,english OP S,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't notice my styled hair
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.01,0:01:23.98,english OP S,,0000,0000,0000,,or my nice set of press-on nails.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.98,0:01:31.36,english OP S,,0000,0000,0000,,Love isn't about the unhappy tears that go along with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.36,0:01:36.07,english OP S,,0000,0000,0000,,Those tears only leave my eyes dry and hurt me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.07,0:01:41.99,english OP S,,0000,0000,0000,,I love this destiny
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.91,0:01:50.88,english OP S,,0000,0000,0000,,between only you and only me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.88,0:01:55.80,english OP S,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to accept your hot feelings
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.01,0:02:02.93,english OP S,,0000,0000,0000,,and be taken by you forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.93,0:02:09.69,english OP S,,0000,0000,0000,,Despite your uncute, tearful face and your shortness, I still love you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.57,0:02:23.74,Episode title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(950,950)\pos(140,384)}Episode 4 ...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.12,0:02:24.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's the one I love.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.04,0:02:28.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.00,0:02:33.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have your lines down pat?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.04,0:02:34.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.88,0:02:44.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it just my imagination, or has he seemed distant lately?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.14,0:02:47.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's been like this ever since the day we had those steamed meat buns...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.48,0:02:48.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Yano.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.48,0:02:49.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's up?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.44,0:02:50.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You see...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.52,0:02:54.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A happy dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.11,0:02:54.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.24,0:03:00.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's happiness...?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.66,0:03:02.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.87,0:03:03.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a tough one.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.49,0:03:05.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.58,0:03:06.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uhh...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.08,0:03:11.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah! Something warm.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.12,0:03:11.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something warm?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.92,0:03:14.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Like a steamed meat bun or a roasted sweet potato.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.54,0:03:16.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something that warms you up on a cold day.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.13,0:03:19.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something that soothes your heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.05,0:03:20.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A steamed meat bun, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.13,0:03:23.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it can be anything, like a book you like or a CD.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.14,0:03:25.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or someone you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.82,0:03:37.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go get some steamed meat buns.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.99,0:03:47.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nana, that ring's really cute.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.03,0:03:49.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Ah, this?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.20,0:03:51.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! It's adorable!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.17,0:03:53.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.25,0:03:54.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's glass, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.50,0:03:57.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who did you force into buying that for you? Really!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.42,0:04:00.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I bought it myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.01,0:04:05.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Buying a ring for yourself... is pretty sad, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.14,0:04:06.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.14,0:04:08.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.22,0:04:11.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.56,0:04:14.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez! I can't believe this!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.48,0:04:17.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's running. What are we gonna do about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.36,0:04:19.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah... that really sucks.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.69,0:04:21.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That'll have to be completely redrawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.57,0:04:22.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're so mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.86,0:04:24.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After it was looking so good, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.74,0:04:27.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're out of time now. What are we gonna do?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.95,0:04:29.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to have to buy new paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.99,0:04:31.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unless we have any leftover...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.41,0:04:32.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Should I help out?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.34,0:04:40.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? You don't mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.84,0:04:44.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nope. I'm free right now, and it's just some painting, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.43,0:04:45.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks a ton!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.01,0:04:47.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yano's pretty nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.72,0:04:49.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How unusual...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.35,0:04:52.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yamamoto-san, could you get a brush for Yano?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.07,0:05:04.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're always slacking off, and you only pretend to be helpful at times like these.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.32,0:05:09.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're pretty good at that, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.29,0:05:20.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I... I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.29,0:05:23.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, since he's the lead in the play, he must be having the toughest time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.42,0:05:27.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that he's skipped a lot of rehearsals, but he also memorizes his lines quickly...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.59,0:05:29.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...so he's getting done what needs to be done.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.51,0:05:31.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Takahashi-san, you're too easy on Yano.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.19,0:05:39.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is kind of weird, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.19,0:05:41.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whenever anyone says anything to Yano...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.77,0:05:46.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...he avoids the question or shuts them up. It's always one or the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.40,0:05:49.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But when Yamamoto-san said that stuff to him, he didn't respond at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.78,0:05:51.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that weird?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.70,0:05:54.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think it could be because of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.25,0:05:55.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's Nana-san's little sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.91,0:05:56.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's history between them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.38,0:06:02.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nana-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.59,0:06:06.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...was the girl Yano was going out with in middle school.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.97,0:06:10.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But last year, she died in a car accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.14,0:06:14.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I don't get!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.60,0:06:16.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the big deal? She's just the little sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.35,0:06:19.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like it was Yano's fault her older sister died.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.31,0:06:22.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He should be the one blaming other people!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.06,0:06:24.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not only did she betray him, but then she went and died!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.86,0:06:28.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really, Yano should be the one holding a grudge, not Yamamoto-san!
